observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the City Accountant: 

Coordinate with the Source Agency concerned to determine and confirm the accuracy of the amounts reflected in the Due to LGU and Due to NGA accounts;

Identify the fund transfers wherein the intended programs/projects have been completed, terminated, cancelled or abandoned in order to identify which funds are due to be returned;


Prepare and update schedules on the composition of the Due to LGU and Due to NGA accounts to support the book balances.  Prepare adjusting entries to reclassify recording of erroneous fund transfers.


We also recommended that the City Treasurer determine the availability of cash of all fund transfers which are reported in the books and issue the check in favor of the Source Agencies to return all unutilized amount.  In case the source agency can no longer be identified, the check shall be made in favor of the Bureau of Treasury.

We recommended that the City Mayor: 

Require the City Assessor to:

conduct continuous ocular inspections at the barangay level to validate the actual use of the real properties;

update the Assessment Rolls as to the conditions of the real properties, the exact addresses and identity of declared owners, the exemptions on RPT, if any;

update continuously the City’s records particularly on the Tax Declarations issued and check if there are clerical errors due to General Revisions.

Direct the City Treasurer to:

develop an effective Tax Collection Campaign program to intensify and maximize collection of RPT/SET Receivables;

deputize bonded Barangay Treasurers, to collect all taxes on real property located in the Barangay;

prepare a certified list of all real property tax delinquencies and post quarterly the said list at the City Hall and in a publicly accessible and conspicuous place in each barangay;

issue a notice of delinquency to each concerned property owner;


submit the certified list of all real property tax delinquencies, with a statement of the reasons for such non-payment, to the Sanggunian concerned on or before December thirty-first (31st) of the year, with a request for assistance in the enforcement of the remedies for collection either by administrative action through levy on real property or by judicial action.

We also recommended that the City Mayor mandate every employee of the City to coordinate with and assist the City Treasurer in her campaign to increase collections of real property taxes.
